POD1000000004_S0000083	In the early days, all the founders had to hustle like this. Before they had staff, it was Salzburg, Pappas, and Wadiak packing up boxes in a small kitchen in Long Island City, New York.
POD1000000004_S0000084	Then, seemingly out of nowhere, the company landed some sweet venture capital to the tune of $3 million. Things were looking good for the startup.
POD1000000004_S0000085	Within the first few years, the business took off. In 2014, Blue Apron was shipping 600,000 meals a month. By 2016, it was 8 million meals and a billion dollars in revenue.
POD1000000004_S0000086	Within just five years of its founding, the company employed 4,500 people and was valued at nearly $2 billion. Blue Apron looked like it was on the express train to successville.
