POD1000000010_S0000171	and you'll be less likely to lash out violently in frustration or anger.
POD1000000010_S0000172	Self-regulation is something we all struggle with.
POD1000000010_S0000173	And that's why mindfulness is so important and really learning how to manage our own emotions.
POD1000000010_S0000174	And I think the earlier that we can practice those skills, the better we'll be in adulthood.
POD1000000010_S0000175	In fact, the folks at Sesame are so convinced of the connection between mindfulness and kindness that they like to use a special word, kindfulness.
POD1000000010_S0000176	You hear that Miriam Webster?
POD1000000010_S0000178	Anyway, lots of these social and emotional learning programs introduce tools like meditation, relaxation, yoga, to help kids work on this body-mind connection.
POD1000000010_S0000179	So we talked about the courage that it takes to step in when someone else is hurting, even if that person is being hurtful towards you.
POD1000000010_S0000180	and how to cultivate that quiet in your mind that lets you do that.
