POD1000000033_S0000013	So going into this research, we knew that states faced similar challenges in increasing access to broadband, but we learned that they're also taking similar approaches but adapting them to their needs. That's really where those categories came from, those groupings.
POD1000000033_S0000014	If you look at goals, for example, you have states like Minnesota and West Virginia where their statewide broadband goals are focused on border-to-border universal coverage.
POD1000000033_S0000015	Then you look at a state like California that has a goal to connect 98% of the population in each one of its roughly 20 regions.
POD1000000033_S0000016	How do you hope that a tool like this can help close the digital divide in terms of broadband access?
