POD1000000048_S0000213	people avoid besides not neglecting the areas in which they're weak. And don't try and rest on your laurels in, say, technical areas or policy areas, because it's a fairly interdisciplinary area.
POD1000000048_S0000214	and you would need to think about what sorts of disciplinary perspectives would be beneficial to solving the problem you're interested in and not just what is your background, though of course you wanna draw on your strengths.
POD1000000048_S0000215	I guess because it's a field that's at its fairly early stages and is growing quickly.
POD1000000048_S0000216	It would be a good fit for someone who was really able to set their own direction and meet people and potentially attract funding to do what they want to do. Someone who's going to create the opportunities that they want to go into.
POD1000000048_S0000217	Yeah, absolutely. And I, yeah, it's an area that's evolving and I think a lot of the organizations
POD1000000048_S0000218	that exist today, and I have mentioned as, as you know, good, good places to work and so forth, didn't exist five years ago. So,
POD1000000048_S0000220	Yeah, some of them didn't exist one year ago. So it's it's an area in flux. And I think, you know, as with politics,
